radiographic_examinations.findings: Multiloculated, rim enhancing fluid collection in the right lower quadrant measuring 3.5 x 2.6 cm, small locules of extraluminal air, appendicolith at the origin of a dilated appendix measuring 9 mm, reactive lymph nodes, collapse and reactive thickening of the terminal ileum. The imaged lung bases show no pleural effusion. The liver enhances homogeneously with an area of hypodensity likely representing focal fatty infiltration and a punctate hyperdensity likely indicating a biliary hamartoma. No concerning focal liver lesions or bowel obstruction.
